this is also resurrected from a deleted poem love it hate it indifference broken left alone to live out life far away from any peace all alone with just your mind a most awful dreadful place try to escape there is none locked away to live then die wrap that thought around your brain enough to drive you insane total silence not a sound just the thoughts within your head enough to make you crazy just you your cries and four walls blood runs down the walls all day all night rattle rusty chains finally a speck of hope through the darkness hangs a rope is gruesome morbid and dark it does look like prison a torture chamber i like the poem pretty good hooray for the dark prince of poetry marilyn your angel YuYu Hakusho Sin City Alice Cooper Time Out of Mind Professional wrestling match types Angel Sanctuary Charles Bukowski John Berryman Spike (Buffy the Vampire Slayer) The Wall Jean Grey Jon Secada Night (book) Supporting Characters (Xenogears) Escape from New York The Suffering (game) Yehuda Halevi Books of Blood Timeline of alternative rock The Amber Spyglass Marilyn Monroe The Catcher in the Rye Hell Minor characters in Sonic the Hedgehog Pitaten Luminoth The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy (film) Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Great Fire of London Pink Floyd Capital punishment Salad Fingers Crucifixion Jason Voorhees The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Fire Emblem: Blazing Sword StarCraft Secret Missions Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix Fitz Hugh Ludlow Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind W.I.T.C.H. Farscape Professional wrestling holds Paul Revere's Ride Socrates Charles Manson Races in the Warcraft universe The Rise and Fall of Ziggy Stardust and the Spiders from Mars Hole (band) Knots Landing William Cowper Galvatron The Death Gate Cycle Adam Mickiewicz Days of our Lives Characters of Lost Blade Runner D.N. Angel Blood (computer game) Turandot George Harrison Shaggy dog story Joker (comics) Poetry EastEnders Jack Kerouac AFI 100 Years series Torture Lou